Following the detection of the first case of Corona Virus, brought in by an Italian, Speaker of Lagos State House of Assembly, Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa, on Monday called on the Lagos State government to establish Institute for Cancer and Disease Control to cater for cases like Coronavirus, Ebola and other related diseases. The speaker made this known during plenary in support of a motion moved by Hon. Sokunle on the need for government to take proactive measures in order to curb spread of the Corona virus. According to him, the Institute should be well equipped to manage situations arising from cases such as corona virus instead making hurried measures whenever such cases arise. While commending government for efforts so far made to nip the problem of coronavirus in bud, he enjoined the governor to strengthen sensitization awareness in public and private schools. The Speaker further noted that as had been stated by health experts and stressed by the federal and Lagos state governments, the ailment only causes mild illnesses that are easily treated and can only be severe if there are underlying chronic health challenges. According to him, “It is always better to wash our hands, stay a distance from those who are sneezing and coughing as well as other such simple instructions,”. Obasa urged residents to promptly report suspected cases adding that the Assembly would soon meet over the development. The Deputy Speaker, Hon. Wasiu Eshinlokun in his contributions enjoined the local governments corporate bodies and private organizations to installed hand sanitizers at strategic locations of their premises. Hon. Mojisolaoluwa Alli Macaulay in her remark decried the attitude of some Nigerians who took advantage of the announcement of the emergence of Corona Virus to increase prizes of Hand Sanitizers adding that people should imbibe culture of been our brothers keepers. 